03:52.000 --> 03:54.000
- Get the cross.
- I've got it.

03:56.000 --> 03:58.000
Oh, Christ! Go back. Go back.

03:58.035 --> 04:00.000
Go back.

04:01.000 --> 04:03.000
Get the sniper!

04:09.000 --> 04:12.000
Yeah, yeah, I got him.

04:12.035 --> 04:13.000
Get the priest.

04:13.035 --> 04:15.000
Is he mad?

04:22.000 --> 04:23.000
Is he mad?

04:26.000 --> 04:26.965
Come on.

04:27.000 --> 04:29.000
- You don't want this?
- Come on!

05:03.000 --> 05:05.000
This is the wrong street.

05:18.000 --> 05:20.000
Let's go back.

05:22.000 --> 05:24.000
- Michael, let's go back.
- It's here.

05:29.000 --> 05:30.000
Shit!

05:42.000 --> 05:45.000
They put roadblocks.
I turned the van round.

05:45.035 --> 05:48.000
Others are going to be
stuck here for hours.

05:51.000 --> 05:53.000
Easy!

06:01.000 --> 06:04.965
- What did you get?
- We need a new driver.

06:05.000 --> 06:10.000
It was hard to get Joey. He was
a cabbie. He knows the city.

06:10.035 --> 06:11.965
He's an idiot.

06:12.000 --> 06:14.965
He's been selling our petrol.
AND he's an idiot.

06:15.000 --> 06:19.000
We've been running round the
streets trying to find him.

06:19.035 --> 06:21.965
Is that true about the petrol?

06:22.000 --> 06:25.000
It was full this morning
and it's empty now.

06:27.000 --> 06:29.000
That's it. From there.

06:29.035 --> 06:31.000
Now, another three.

06:32.000 --> 06:35.000
No one dares move the body.

06:35.035 --> 06:35.965
Then the boy.

06:36.000 --> 06:38.965
- This now.
- No, the boy.

06:39.000 --> 06:43.000
I just saw this footage
of Flynn being shot at.

06:43.035 --> 06:44.965
- Got that?
- No.

06:45.000 --> 06:47.000
- Why not?
- Why not what?

06:47.035 --> 06:49.965
Why haven't we got it?

06:50.000 --> 06:51.965
General decline
in journalistic standards.

06:52.000 --> 06:56.000
It's this news as entertainment
bollocks. So patronising.

06:56.035 --> 06:59.000
- I hate that.
- I hate that, too.

06:59.035 --> 06:59.965
Jane?

07:00.000 --> 07:02.500
I actually think it was very brave,

07:02.535 --> 07:05.000
and most people respond to bravery.

07:05.035 --> 07:07.000
Ooh!

07:09.000 --> 07:11.965
'They were
yards from the church

07:12.000 --> 07:16.000
'when the sniper opened fire,
and now the mother is dead.

07:16.035 --> 07:18.000
'Another innocent victim
killed in cold blood.

07:18.035 --> 07:19.965
'This is Jordan Flynn in Sarajevo. '

07:20.000 --> 07:26.000
I'm not worthy of
applause, but I'll take money.

07:26.035 --> 07:28.000
Oh, thank you.
You'll be remembered.

07:28.035 --> 07:29.965
Thank you so much.

07:30.000 --> 07:32.500
Oh-ho! Well, look
who's here - Henderson.

07:32.535 --> 07:35.000
And Gregg.
Care to make a contribution?

07:35.035 --> 07:37.965
I don't have anything small enough.

07:38.000 --> 07:41.000
Sure you do,
but I was thinking about money.

07:41.035 --> 07:43.965
- What d'you think? Syndicated worldwide.
- Your producers must be delighted

07:44.000 --> 07:49.000
- Exactly.
- They sent you to get killed.

07:49.035 --> 07:51.017
Now it looks like you will.

07:51.052 --> 07:52.965
- Good one!
- Good night.

07:53.000 --> 07:55.000
Henderson, how about
a little Bushmills?

07:55.035 --> 07:57.000
Hey, Gregg - Bushmills.

07:57.035 --> 07:58.965
See ya.

07:59.000 --> 08:02.000
I can't believe
you're turning down Bushmills.

08:02.035 --> 08:04.000
There's a first.

08:07.000 --> 08:10.000
He was only trying to help.

08:10.035 --> 08:12.000
We're here to report.

08:12.035 --> 08:12.965
Yeah.

08:13.000 --> 08:17.000
Haven't seen Bushmills
in a long time.

08:17.035 --> 08:19.000
Michael, are you all right?

08:20.000 --> 08:23.000
- Michael, are you all right?
- Yeah.

08:24.000 --> 08:26.000
Good.

08:28.000 --> 08:32.500
- We're gonna drink to the line.
- Lower... please. Better.

08:32.534 --> 08:37.000
I make my important decisions
after reaching that line.

08:37.034 --> 08:40.000
I liked what you did.
It was really brave.

08:40.034 --> 08:42.017
- It stank.
- Ooh, God!

08:42.052 --> 08:43.965
You thought it stank?

08:44.000 --> 08:46.965
It wasn't about Sarajevo,
it was about YOU.

08:47.000 --> 08:51.000
Back home no one's heard of
Sarajevo but they all know me.

08:51.035 --> 08:53.517
- She with you?
- Freelance.

08:53.552 --> 08:55.965
Figures. Who would hire her?

08:56.000 --> 08:59.000
You should never drink
serious whisky without water

08:59.035 --> 09:01.000
because the strength of the alcohol

09:01.035 --> 09:03.000
smothers the complex flavour.

09:03.035 --> 09:04.965
Is that right?

09:05.000 --> 09:06.000
- Chiverly!
- Chiverly!

09:11.000 --> 09:11.965
Cheers.

09:12.000 --> 09:16.000
I am in love with you. In spite
of the company you keep.

09:16.035 --> 09:17.965
Thank you.

09:18.000 --> 09:19.965
I'd like to save you from this.

09:20.000 --> 09:24.000
Leaving so soon, Mr Flynn?
The war is young.

09:26.000 --> 09:27.965
- Hi.
- Zeljko.

09:28.000 --> 09:30.000
I got your phone-call, sir.

09:30.035 --> 09:31.965
Ah!

09:32.000 --> 09:34.000
Try - you might be lucky.

09:34.035 --> 09:36.000
Very good. Here.

09:36.035 --> 09:39.965
Oh. Thanks.

09:40.000 --> 09:41.000
- Here.
- Thanks.

09:41.035 --> 09:42.517
Thank you.

09:42.552 --> 09:43.965
- Bye.
- Bye.

09:44.000 --> 09:47.000
- 'Hello?'
- Helen, hi, it's me.

09:49.000 --> 09:51.000
- 'Shit, sorry. '
- Helen?

09:51.035 --> 09:53.000
'Yeah, hang on.

09:54.000 --> 09:58.000
'Sorry. I was putting
the kids to bed. '

09:58.035 --> 09:58.965
It's OK.

09:59.000 --> 10:01.000
'I must've fallen asleep.

10:04.000 --> 10:05.965
- 'Hello?'
- You OK?

10:06.000 --> 10:10.000
'Yeah, I'm... I'm fine. Fine.

10:10.035 --> 10:10.965
'What time is it?'

10:11.000 --> 10:16.000
Er, it's... well, you're an hour
behind - it's twenty past ten.

10:16.035 --> 10:19.000
- 'She's awake again. '
- 'Mummy!'

10:19.035 --> 10:22.000
- 'Can you hear that?'
- Yeah. All right. You'd better go.

10:22.035 --> 10:24.000
Um, I just...

10:24.035 --> 10:25.965
'Mummy!'

10:26.000 --> 10:27.500
I'm all right.

10:27.535 --> 10:29.000
'I'm coming!'

10:34.000 --> 10:37.000
(# Stone Roses: "I Wanna Be Adored")

12:25.000 --> 12:25.965
In English.

12:26.000 --> 12:30.000
Everything in English
this morning. Gotta practise.

12:32.000 --> 12:34.000
This is my last clean one.

12:34.035 --> 12:35.965
Thanks.

12:36.000 --> 12:39.000
It's from Marks & Spencer in Paris.

12:39.035 --> 12:41.017
You don't believe it?

12:41.052 --> 12:43.000
- No.
- What's this?

13:04.000 --> 13:07.000
Certainly is
a woman of experience.

13:07.035 --> 13:10.000
- Uh, Jane Carson?
- Risto Bavic?

13:10.035 --> 13:13.000
- Yes.
- Come and join us.

13:14.000 --> 13:17.500
Um, Michael Henderson'll
be along shortly.

13:17.535 --> 13:20.965
This is our new driver.
This is Flynn.

13:21.000 --> 13:25.000
- Hi. Nice to meet you.
- Hey! Dig those threads.

13:25.035 --> 13:29.517
Yeah. It's a great colour.
Sort of unusual.

13:29.552 --> 13:34.000
My man, Zeljko!
Thank you. Do you have it?

13:34.005 --> 13:34.995
- Oh, brother!
- Four.

13:35.000 --> 13:38.000
- I'll find Michael.
- Take 'em.

13:38.035 --> 13:41.000
- This is fine.
- Suit yourself.

13:52.000 --> 13:55.000
For the head.
You need a hangover cure?

13:55.035 --> 13:58.000
Would you mind
if I save it till later?

13:58.035 --> 14:00.000
I haven't started my hangover yet.

14:00.035 --> 14:02.017
Go ahead. Here, take...

14:02.052 --> 14:03.965
All I need's one. Take 'em.

14:04.000 --> 14:06.000
He's here now.
His English is pretty good.

14:06.035 --> 14:08.517
He studied in Birmingham or Bristol.

14:08.552 --> 14:11.000
- Hi, Mr Henderson.
- Man at C&A.

14:11.035 --> 14:13.017
- Marks & Spencer.
- What?

14:13.052 --> 14:14.965
C&A do a similar colour -

14:15.000 --> 14:17.000
only Marks & Spencer do THIS colour.

14:17.035 --> 14:19.000
Michael, mortar attack. Come on.

14:19.035 --> 14:21.000
Joke.

14:23.000 --> 14:27.000
That's four days in a row
I haven't had breakfast.

15:03.000 --> 15:04.000
Hey!

15:05.000 --> 15:07.000
Hail the conquering hero!

15:14.000 --> 15:16.000
- Egg!
- Thank you.

15:16.035 --> 15:17.965
- Two.
- Two eggs!

15:18.000 --> 15:21.000
- Two eggs is a miracle!
- Three eggs!

15:21.035 --> 15:23.000
Is there a word for three eggs?

15:23.035 --> 15:24.965
- Omelette.
- Very good.

15:25.000 --> 15:28.000
- Omelette!
- That's right. Omelette.

16:25.000 --> 16:26.000
It's in Facie Miska.

16:27.000 --> 16:29.500
- Know it?
- Yeah, of course.

16:29.535 --> 16:32.000
OK. You drive. Who's got the keys?

16:42.000 --> 16:44.000
Can I bum a lift?

16:44.035 --> 16:45.965
Hi. Annie McGee.

16:46.000 --> 16:48.000
Shall we make a move?

17:06.000 --> 17:10.000
I know this probably
isn't the best time,

17:10.035 --> 17:12.517
but I'm working on a story.

17:12.551 --> 17:14.964
I need papers, transport...

17:15.000 --> 17:18.000
Talk to Jane Carson.
She's the producer.

17:18.035 --> 17:20.000
I'm just the journalist.

17:20.005 --> 17:20.994
- Smoke?
- No.

17:21.000 --> 17:23.964
This could be
a very important story.

17:24.000 --> 17:27.000
More important than
bombing people in the street?

17:27.035 --> 17:30.000
Compared to that, it seems
like fucking Jane Austen.

17:30.035 --> 17:32.000
Really? I never fucked Jane Austen.

19:03.000 --> 19:03.995
Get the vegetables, Gregg.

19:04.000 --> 19:08.000
Gregg, get the vegetables,
can you? And the bags.

19:08.035 --> 19:10.000
This guy with the eye, Gregg...

19:14.000 --> 19:15.965
Gregg!

19:16.000 --> 19:19.000
What's the guy's name?
What's the... driver's name?

19:19.035 --> 19:21.000
- Risto.
- Risto!

19:23.000 --> 19:25.000
Risto!

19:26.000 --> 19:27.500
What's she saying?

19:27.535 --> 19:28.965
What's she saying?

19:29.000 --> 19:31.000
She doesn't know what she's saying.

19:31.035 --> 19:32.965
She's lost control.

19:33.000 --> 19:34.590
- You shouldn't film her.
- Get the bread.

19:43.005 --> 19:44.000
Risto!

20:03.000 --> 20:04.000
What?

20:06.000 --> 20:06.995
Don't understand. Risto!

20:07.000 --> 20:11.000
Can you ask this girl what she wants?
Ask what she wants.

20:19.000 --> 20:21.000
Both the parents are dead.

20:27.000 --> 20:30.000
We'll have to tell her.

20:30.035 --> 20:31.000
Yeah.

20:39.000 --> 20:43.000
Does she have any brothers
or sisters who could take her?

20:46.000 --> 20:50.000
Any relatives
we can give her a lift to?

21:07.000 --> 21:09.000
Spooling back.

21:09.035 --> 21:11.000
Roll tape.

21:13.000 --> 21:15.965
We're rolling.

21:16.000 --> 21:17.965
This isn't the lead story.

21:18.000 --> 21:21.000
No,
this is not the lead story.

21:21.035 --> 21:25.000
What IS the lead story?

21:25.035 --> 21:26.965
The Second Coming?

21:27.000 --> 21:30.000
The Duke and Duchess of York
are getting divorced.

21:30.035 --> 21:33.000
Or separated.
I can't remember which.

21:33.005 --> 21:34.000
Excellent!

21:38.000 --> 21:42.000
Michael! Hear your network
had a big scoop today.

21:42.035 --> 21:45.000
Duke and Duchess of Pork,
or something?

21:45.035 --> 21:46.965
By the way, your Queen...

21:47.000 --> 21:52.000
She's the richest woman in the
world, but what does she do?

22:07.000 --> 22:09.000
- I'll drive.
- OK.

23:18.000 --> 23:21.000
