'One day my mum went to work

29:20.000 --> 29:23.000
'and was told she couldn't
work there any more

29:23.035 --> 29:24.965
'because she was a Muslim.

29:25.000 --> 29:29.000
'Then it was announced
that all Muslims had to leave.

29:33.000 --> 29:36.000
'There was shelling,
all sorts of things.

29:36.035 --> 29:38.017
'There were dead people around.

29:38.052 --> 29:40.000
'I've got nothing to say about it.

29:40.035 --> 29:42.000
'It was terrible. '

29:51.000 --> 29:55.000
'Where my house is.
I'd like to go back there. '

30:02.000 --> 30:02.995
Yours, yeah?

30:03.000 --> 30:05.000
Hello. Yours, yeah?

30:11.000 --> 30:14.000
She ask if this
is where you come from.

30:14.035 --> 30:16.965
Ah! Yes. Yes.

30:17.000 --> 30:19.000
It's changed a bit since then.

30:22.000 --> 30:23.965
She want to get out of Sarajevo.

30:24.000 --> 30:27.000
Your film would help
to get us out of here?

30:29.000 --> 30:31.000
Yes. I hope so.

30:32.000 --> 30:34.000
She wants a promise.

30:34.035 --> 30:36.000
It's a promise.

31:03.000 --> 31:06.000
It's a Haggadah.
It's the story of the Exodus.

31:06.035 --> 31:06.965
Oh.

31:07.000 --> 31:11.000
It was in the museum. When
the Nazis came, it disappeared.

31:11.035 --> 31:14.017
When the war was over, it was back.

31:14.052 --> 31:16.526
And now it's disappeared again.

31:16.561 --> 31:18.965
- It's lovely.
- Yeah, it's nice.

31:19.000 --> 31:23.000
On the real one you can see
fingerprints and wine stains

31:23.005 --> 31:23.995
where it's been used.

31:24.000 --> 31:28.000
People say that after this war,
it will return.

31:28.035 --> 31:30.000
But it's been sold to buy weapons.

31:30.035 --> 31:31.965
No, that's not true.

31:32.000 --> 31:35.500
When the museum was bombed, the
old guy, Professor Imamovich,

31:35.535 --> 31:39.000
he found the book in the rubble.
Now it's somewhere safe.

31:39.035 --> 31:40.965
It'll be back.

31:41.000 --> 31:46.000
- What are you doing?
- I use books to cook with.

31:47.000 --> 31:49.000
It's all there is.

31:50.000 --> 31:54.000
If you have to burn books,
you should at least enjoy it.

31:54.035 --> 31:57.517
You know - special occasion,
special book.

31:57.552 --> 32:01.000
Besides, I could never
relate to the Exodus.

32:03.000 --> 32:06.000
(# The Happy Mondays: "Donovan")

32:20.000 --> 32:22.965
You know what I'm going to do?

32:23.000 --> 32:26.000
I'm going to make
a concert here in Sarajevo.

32:26.035 --> 32:27.965
Is that such a good idea?

32:28.000 --> 32:32.965
- I will defy death in the name of Art.
- What about the audience?

32:33.000 --> 32:36.000
The audience will die happy
listening to me.

32:36.035 --> 32:38.965
But I'm not going to do it yet,

32:39.000 --> 32:43.000
because Sarajevo is only
the 14th worst place on Earth.

32:43.035 --> 32:46.017
I'm waiting until we're number one.

32:46.052 --> 32:49.000
- What is number one?
- LA, of course.

33:00.000 --> 33:01.965
Help with the babies.

33:02.000 --> 33:04.000
You want the children upstairs?

33:04.035 --> 33:06.000
- Yes.
- OK.

33:11.000 --> 33:13.965
'We came here this evening

33:14.000 --> 33:17.500
'to make another report
on the Ljubica Ivezic Orphanage.

33:17.535 --> 33:20.767
'When we arrived, the building
next door was on fire

33:20.802 --> 33:24.000
'and one room of the orphanage
had been destroyed. '

33:35.000 --> 33:36.000
Roadrunner's coming.

33:37.000 --> 33:40.000
Roadrunner's coming.
Come on. Let's go.

33:50.000 --> 33:51.965
The Bosnian government

33:52.000 --> 33:54.965
is against any kind of evacuation.

33:55.000 --> 33:58.000
From their point of view,
the Serbs want the city empty.

33:58.035 --> 34:01.000
If they evacuate,
we're helping the Serbs.

34:01.035 --> 34:04.000
Evacuation is actually
collaboration,

34:04.035 --> 34:05.965
and that's a quote.

34:06.000 --> 34:10.000
It will take time to find
a solution to the problem.

34:10.034 --> 34:12.000
Thus we must have patience.

34:39.000 --> 34:40.500
This is cold.

34:40.534 --> 34:41.965
Here, have mine.

34:42.000 --> 34:45.500
- Zeljko!
- No, I want a fresh cup.

34:45.534 --> 34:48.766
- Is that hot?
- I want a fresh cup.

34:48.802 --> 34:52.000
- Got a pen?
- Give me your book.

34:54.000 --> 34:56.000
Look at 'em. They're like vultures.

34:57.000 --> 34:59.000
Look at US. We're like vultures.

35:01.000 --> 35:03.000
Working vultures. It's grand.

35:04.000 --> 35:06.000
Great.

35:10.000 --> 35:14.000
That's mine
and Mr Henderson is inside.

35:14.035 --> 35:16.965
- Happy?
- Thanks.

35:17.000 --> 35:19.000
- Thank you.
- OK. Bye.

35:21.000 --> 35:23.000
Just a sec. Thanks.

35:31.000 --> 35:32.965
It's extraordinary, is it not,

35:33.000 --> 35:36.000
that with children trapped
in the most dangerous corner

35:36.035 --> 35:38.965
of the most dangerous city on Earth

35:39.000 --> 35:43.000
that this plane will fly
out of here completely empty.

35:43.035 --> 35:45.965
'It would be a simple matter
to move the children

35:46.000 --> 35:51.000
'but someone somewhere along the
bureaucratic line is saying no. '

36:24.000 --> 36:28.000
Cheer up, Michael.
You'll be back in London by Tuesday.

36:29.000 --> 36:32.000
Put that back.
That's my lucky hat.

36:32.035 --> 36:33.965
Working wonders for us.

36:34.000 --> 36:37.000
Six years in that -
I've never been shot.

36:37.035 --> 36:40.000
Swap it for my lucky knickers?

36:40.035 --> 36:41.965
- No.
- Charming.

36:42.000 --> 36:45.000
I'm not gonna film a war
wearing your knickers.

36:45.035 --> 36:46.965
On your head!

36:47.000 --> 36:49.500
Do they stop you getting shot?

36:49.535 --> 36:52.000
No. I just get lucky wearing them.

36:57.000 --> 36:59.000
Flynn!

37:00.000 --> 37:03.000
Where've you been? Thought
you'd gone to the seaside.

37:03.035 --> 37:05.000
Met a lady who needed a lift.

37:05.035 --> 37:07.017
- Hi, Henderson.
- Hi.

37:07.052 --> 37:09.026
- Annie.
- Get it?

37:09.061 --> 37:10.965
- Yeah.
- Got what?

37:11.000 --> 37:15.000
- Was it terrible?
- Yeah. It WAS terrible.

37:17.000 --> 37:22.000
- Where've you been?
- Uh, Omarska and Trnopolie.

37:22.005 --> 37:23.000
It was... a real party.

37:30.000 --> 37:33.500
'ITN was given
permission to visit these camps

37:33.535 --> 37:37.000
'by Radovan Karadjic,
the Bosnian Serb leader.

37:37.035 --> 37:39.000
'There are 4,500 prisoners held here.

37:40.000 --> 37:44.000
'These are the ones
we were allowed to talk to. '

38:05.000 --> 38:08.000
Can you just hold on?
Hold on. Michael...

38:08.035 --> 38:08.965
Sorry.

38:09.000 --> 38:11.965
I... didn't wanna
let it go and, um...

38:12.000 --> 38:16.000
No, no, no. You did
the right thing. Absolutely.

38:16.035 --> 38:18.000
- Well done.
- Thanks.

38:19.000 --> 38:22.000
Annie, it's a great story.
Congratulations.

38:23.000 --> 38:25.000
Thank you.

38:42.000 --> 38:43.965
Henderson.

38:44.000 --> 38:46.965
- You, uh... you got any petrol?
- Yeah.

38:47.000 --> 38:51.000
You think I might be able
to get a lift across town?

38:51.035 --> 38:53.000
- Now?
- Yeah.

38:54.000 --> 38:55.000
Yeah. All right.

38:55.035 --> 38:57.000
Top man!

39:14.000 --> 39:14.965
Yeah. Uh...

39:15.000 --> 39:18.000
Uh... I got... I was with...

39:34.000 --> 39:35.965
You speak Bosnian, eh?

39:36.000 --> 39:39.500
Describing it in English,
it doesn't sound real.

39:39.535 --> 39:43.000
If any language could
do it justice, it's Bosnian.

39:43.005 --> 39:43.995
And does it?

39:44.000 --> 39:47.000
I'm still learning.
Little, simple things.

39:47.035 --> 39:49.017
Um, "do you have an avocado?"

39:49.052 --> 39:51.000
"I'm desperate for a toilet. "

39:52.000 --> 39:53.965
- Ah!
- Ah.

39:54.000 --> 39:58.000
(Flynn) Little things, you know,
like that. Thank you.

39:58.005 --> 39:59.000
Here's the cake.

40:01.000 --> 40:04.000
- Take the small piece.
- Toast.

40:07.000 --> 40:10.000
- What's that?
- To their son.

40:10.035 --> 40:12.000
Yeah. To your son.

40:40.000 --> 40:42.965
'History has shown us
that you can't allow

40:43.000 --> 40:47.000
'the mass extermination of
people and just let it happen. '

40:49.000 --> 40:52.965
'We do not see
any evidence of a programme

40:53.000 --> 40:56.000
'of systematic or massive
killing of innocent people... '

40:57.000 --> 41:00.000
'50 years ago,
world leaders said,

41:00.035 --> 41:03.000
"'We didn't know what was happening. "

41:03.035 --> 41:05.000
'We know what's happening, now. '

41:11.000 --> 41:12.965
'Don't... Don't live under this dream

41:13.000 --> 41:17.000
'that the West will come
and sort this problem out. '

41:29.000 --> 41:31.000
D'you want these?

41:35.000 --> 41:36.965
What d'you say we smoke one?

41:37.000 --> 41:39.965
Don't start.
Once you start, you never stop.

41:40.000 --> 41:44.000
You're not smoking or
drinking. What ARE you doing?

41:44.005 --> 41:45.000
Staying alive.

41:46.000 --> 41:49.000
Here. Have this as well.

41:52.000 --> 41:57.000
I think I might... I might...
get the hell out and go home.

41:57.035 --> 41:59.000
What d'you think?

41:59.005 --> 41:59.995
Great.

42:00.000 --> 42:02.000
I could... cover
the Republican Convention.

42:02.035 --> 42:03.965
Maybe, uh...

42:04.000 --> 42:05.000
How about, uh, the Superbowl?

42:05.035 --> 42:06.517
Super bollocks!

42:06.552 --> 42:07.965
Super bollocks?

42:08.000 --> 42:10.000
- Why is it when Americans...?
- Why?

42:10.035 --> 42:11.965
Why is it that Americans,

42:12.000 --> 42:15.000
when they're playing sport,
wear so much padding?

42:15.035 --> 42:18.017
You spend more time
dressing up than playing.

42:18.052 --> 42:21.000
Sure, we don't dress
to the nines like cricket.

42:21.035 --> 42:23.965
But... what about basketball?
Just a vest.

42:24.000 --> 42:27.000
Basketball isn't a sport.
Basketball's a freak show.

42:27.035 --> 42:28.965
Easy. You're on sacred territory.

42:29.000 --> 42:32.000
The side with
the tallest player wins.

42:32.035 --> 42:33.965
Also, it's a girls' game.

42:34.000 --> 42:38.000
You know, only two good
things ever came from England.

42:38.035 --> 42:40.000
One - America, two - the Beatles.

42:40.035 --> 42:42.000
Beatles aren't English.

42:43.000 --> 42:44.965
They're from Liverpool.

42:45.000 --> 42:47.000
You even pad up to play girls' games.

42:49.000 --> 42:50.500
You know...

42:50.535 --> 42:52.000
Henderson...

42:53.000 --> 42:56.000
Those orphans are not
your responsibility.

42:56.035 --> 42:58.000
You're here, you're a reporter.

42:58.035 --> 43:02.000
You're here to report.

43:04.000 --> 43:07.000
FUCK YOU! ASSHOLE!

43:07.005 --> 43:08.000
GET A JOB!

43:17.000 --> 43:20.000
Zeljko. Would you take care of these?

43:20.035 --> 43:22.000
Mr Henderson, you leaving?

43:22.035 --> 43:23.965
Yes.

43:24.000 --> 43:26.000
Have some of those. I don't smoke.

43:26.035 --> 43:29.000
- Thank you very much.
- OK.

43:35.000 --> 43:37.000
- Oh, hi there.
- Hi.

43:39.000 --> 43:41.000
- Good night?
- Yeah. Very good.

43:41.035 --> 43:43.965
- Hi.
- This is Nina.

43:44.000 --> 43:48.000
Hello. Welcome to the
14th worst place on Earth.

43:48.005 --> 43:48.995
Thanks.

43:49.000 --> 43:52.000
- Nina's an aid worker.
- Is this water?

43:52.035 --> 43:54.965
- Yeah.
- Can I...?

43:55.000 --> 43:58.000
A children's charity.
The Children's Lifeline.

43:58.035 --> 44:01.000
We've got a bus.
Bring in food and take out kids.

44:01.035 --> 44:04.517
I'm pitching our story
to your network.

44:04.552 --> 44:07.965
- What sort of children?
- Boys and girls.

44:08.000 --> 44:12.000
Children who are sponsored
abroad or have relatives abroad.

44:12.035 --> 44:14.965
And babies.
They're easy to find homes for.

44:15.000 --> 44:19.000
I can get babies. There's an
orphanage on the front line.

44:19.035 --> 44:21.965
- D'you need babies?
- Aren't you leaving?

44:22.000 --> 44:26.000
You COULD leave - with us.
An epic story for you.

44:26.005 --> 44:27.000
The Exodus!

44:39.000 --> 44:41.000
Can you help any of them?

44:43.000 --> 44:46.000
Well... we'll try. We'll try.

44:58.000 --> 44:59.000
It's for the baby.

45:05.000 --> 45:07.000
What's their name?

45:15.000 --> 45:18.000
She thinks that she's going.

45:20.000 --> 45:22.000
She says, "You promised me. "

45:41.000 --> 45:44.000
It's OK if we don't have
birth certificates.

45:48.000 --> 45:49.965
Here they are.

45:50.000 --> 45:54.000
If she had somewhere to go,
could you take her?

45:54.035 --> 45:55.965
- Nina?
- What?

45:56.000 --> 45:58.000
Emira. She wants to leave.

45:58.035 --> 46:00.000
Does she have somewhere to go?

46:02.000 --> 46:04.965
- No.
- No, I can't take her.

46:05.000 --> 46:09.000
We have to prove the older kids
are visiting relatives.

46:09.035 --> 46:10.965
No evacuation - that was the deal.

46:11.000 --> 46:15.000
- What if she was visiting me?
- What d'you mean?

46:15.035 --> 46:19.000
If she was coming to London
to visit me...?

46:19.035 --> 46:21.000
It's not that simple.

46:28.000 --> 46:31.000
Mrs Savic?

46:34.000 --> 46:38.000
I can't speak for her.
You have to ask her yourself.

46:47.000 --> 46:49.000
What's that?
Is that a yes?

46:49.035 --> 46:50.965
Yes. That's yes.

46:51.000 --> 46:54.000
I thought she might want to stay.

46:54.035 --> 46:56.000
She's been with me always.

46:57.000 --> 46:59.965
But it's OK. I'm glad she doesn't.

47:00.000 --> 47:04.000
It's just for a short time.
Until the war's over.

47:04.035 --> 47:05.965
Yeah...

47:06.000 --> 47:09.000
For a short time. I hope so.

47:14.000 --> 47:14.995
Hello, TV man.

47:15.000 --> 47:16.000
You got any cigarettes?

47:48.000 --> 47:51.000
You know this is
completely illegal, don't you?

47:51.005 --> 47:52.000
Yes.

47:54.000 --> 47:57.000
Why are you doing this?

47:58.000 --> 47:58.995
I don't know.

47:59.000 --> 48:01.500
- Married?
- Yes.

48:01.535 --> 48:04.000
- Kids?
- Yes.

48:05.000 --> 48:08.000
OK. I don't want anyone
to know what you're doing.

48:08.035 --> 48:11.000
Not your news crew,
your producer, no one.

48:11.035 --> 48:13.965
Don't sit near her on the bus.

48:14.000 --> 48:17.000
I want you to treat Emira
like all the other kids.

48:17.035 --> 48:19.000
Right.

48:23.000 --> 48:25.000
I'm very grateful.

48:28.000 --> 48:30.965
'At last
there is good news

48:31.000 --> 48:34.000
'for the children of
Ljubica Ivezic Orphanage.

48:34.035 --> 48:37.000
'Five babies have got places
on a convoy

48:37.005 --> 48:37.995
'taking children to Italy,

48:38.000 --> 48:40.965
'where they can stay
till the fighting is over.

48:41.000 --> 48:46.000
'They'll have to leave behind
more than 100 older children

48:46.035 --> 48:47.965
'who aren't so lucky.

48:48.000 --> 48:51.000
'Their daily struggle
to survive seems without end. '

48:52.000 --> 48:54.965
'The babies are not
out of danger yet.

48:55.000 --> 48:58.500
'Landmines and mortars
are some of the hazards

48:58.535 --> 49:01.965
'that lie between them
and the safety of Italy.

49:02.000 --> 49:08.000
'Last week, snipers fired on
a bus trying to leave Sarajevo.

49:08.035 --> 49:10.000
'Two babies were killed. '

49:11.000 --> 49:14.000
Are you worried
about the children?

49:14.005 --> 49:14.995
Yes, I am.

49:15.000 --> 49:18.965
But we have a one-hour
ceasefire throughout Sarajevo

49:19.000 --> 49:22.000
and permission from authorities
on both sides to bring them.

49:22.035 --> 49:25.000
What's the alternative?
To leave them here?

49:26.000 --> 49:27.965
'The mothers of the children
leaving today

49:28.000 --> 49:33.000
'clearly feel it is more
dangerous to stay than to go. '

49:52.000 --> 49:55.000
I'd like to apologise
on behalf of the American people

49:55.035 --> 49:57.965
for not delivering
on those air strikes.

49:58.000 --> 50:01.000
If things were reversed -
Muslims slaughtering Christians,

50:01.035 --> 50:04.000
we'd have done something by now.

51:11.000 --> 51:14.000
We have safe passage
through this street.

51:15.000 --> 51:16.000
This is the street, right?

51:18.000 --> 51:19.000
Door, please.

51:21.000 --> 51:23.500
- Back!
- What's happening?

51:23.535 --> 51:25.965
They won't let us through.

51:26.000 --> 51:28.500
They're sending us
the long way round.

51:28.535 --> 51:31.000
Everybody back!
Back on the bus, please.

52:28.000 --> 52:32.000
Sorry about this. They insist
on searching the bus.

52:32.035 --> 52:34.017
You'll have to get everybody off.

52:34.052 --> 52:36.000
OK, they wanna search the bus.

52:37.000 --> 52:40.000
We have to get off. It'll be OK.

52:59.000 --> 53:02.000
Back on. We're all right.
We're OK. We're going.

53:42.000 --> 53:45.000
It's... It's really like
where I come from.

53:46.000 --> 53:51.000
Apart from the mountains
and the water and the sun.

53:51.005 --> 53:52.000
Very, very similar.

53:53.000 --> 53:55.000
Elton John.

54:49.000 --> 54:50.000
OK.

55:00.000 --> 55:01.965
It's so quiet.

55:02.000 --> 55:05.000
- Treetop.
- Treetop.

55:05.035 --> 55:06.517
Tree top.

55:06.552 --> 55:08.000
Tree... top.

55:08.005 --> 55:08.995
Top.

55:09.000 --> 55:11.965
You'd be better off
teaching her Italian.

55:12.000 --> 55:15.000
- That's where she's going.
- You know Italian?

55:18.000 --> 55:21.000
- Look... tree...
- Tree.

55:21.035 --> 55:23.017
- Top.
- Top.

55:23.052 --> 55:25.000
- Helen.
- Helen.

55:26.000 --> 55:29.000
- Christopher.
- Christopher.

55:29.035 --> 55:30.965
- Jane.
- Jane.

55:31.000 --> 55:33.000
- Garden...
- Garden...

55:33.035 --> 55:34.517
- In...
- In...

55:34.552 --> 55:35.965
- London.
- London.

55:36.000 --> 55:38.000
- London in...
- London in...

55:38.035 --> 55:40.517
- England.
- England.

55:40.552 --> 55:43.000
- England in...
- London.

55:43.005 --> 55:44.000
No...

56:01.000 --> 56:02.000
Good night.

57:09.000 --> 57:10.965
We... give full guarantees

57:11.000 --> 57:14.000
according to Geneva Convention
for civilians.

57:20.000 --> 57:22.000
You can't negotiate with a terrorist.

57:50.000 --> 57:52.000
- Quickly, quickly.
- Onto the bus.

57:52.035 --> 57:53.965
That's it, that's it.

57:54.000 --> 57:58.000
Get 'em on the back door. Come on!

57:58.035 --> 58:00.000
Let's go! Quickly! Come on!

58:41.000 --> 58:43.000
Chetniks.

58:54.000 --> 58:56.500
We've got documentation here

58:56.535 --> 58:58.767
from your people in Pale.

58:58.802 --> 59:00.901
- Pale, eh?
- That's right.

59:00.936 --> 59:03.468
There's, uh, the official seal.

59:03.503 --> 59:05.965
I have the rest
of the documents.

59:06.000 --> 59:10.000
That's permission to go through
all the different territories.

59:10.035 --> 59:13.000
Be cool, it'll be fine.

59:25.000 --> 59:27.965
Oh, oh, oh. We have no Muslims.

59:28.000 --> 59:32.000
No Muslim children
on this bus. No Muslims.

59:34.000 --> 59:36.000
We have no Muslim children...

59:36.035 --> 59:37.965
OK!

59:38.000 --> 59:41.000
Why is he taking these kids?

59:47.000 --> 59:52.000
We have documents for these
children. They are not Muslim!

59:53.000 --> 59:54.965
What's he saying?

59:55.000 --> 59:59.000
What does he want?
I'll give it to him!

01:00:04.000 --> 01:00:05.965
Munira, tell him now,

01:00:06.000 --> 01:00:10.000
we have papers to get us
through this territory.

01:00:12.000 --> 01:00:16.000
We have documents for each
and every child on this bus.

01:00:23.000 --> 01:00:26.000
No, no. She's English. She's with me.

01:00:26.005 --> 01:00:27.000
She's English!

01:00:42.000 --> 01:00:43.000
Emira! Stop!

01:00:44.000 --> 01:00:46.000
Stay here.

01:00:47.000 --> 01:00:49.000
Where are they taking them?!

01:00:51.000 --> 01:00:53.000
Stay. Stay.

01:01:45.000 --> 01:01:47.000
There wasn't anything you could do.

01:03:01.000 --> 01:03:03.000
Can you swim?

01:03:13.000 --> 01:03:15.000
Leila!

01:03:30.000 --> 01:03:33.000
Looks like you missed the boat, kid.

01:03:33.035 --> 01:03:36.000
